Sara in a hollow redwood



This burnt-out tree had three entrances: a long slit from which I took the picture, the one behind Sara,
and a smaller one to the right. From the outside it just looked like a healthy tree.
Taken Monday, June 25, 2001, 09:56:23am.  Original image size: 1200x1600, 1025kb
Technical details: Olympus C700UZ, 1/2s @ F2.8, ISO 800, 38mm
PS6 Clone red spot, iSORemover1, Saturate +20, USM 20:100 - 20:20:2, EdgeSharpen
